  <div class="form-grid">
    <section>
      <h2>What Bankroll IQ Collects</h2>
      <p>Bankroll IQ stores the information you provide directly, including account details, bet entries, bankroll settings, notes, and CSV imports. The app may also store technical information required to keep you signed in and operate securely, such as session data and password reset tokens.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How Information Is Used</h2>
      <p>Your information is used to provide the product features you expect, including account access, bet tracking, bankroll analysis, exports, imports, and security-related flows like login protection and password reset.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What Bankroll IQ Does Not Do</h2>
      <p>Bankroll IQ is a tracking and analytics tool. It does not place wagers, operate as a sportsbook, or guarantee betting outcomes. Bankroll IQ is not intended to provide legal, tax, or financial advice.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Sharing</h2>
      <p>Bankroll IQ does not sell your personal information. Information may be shared only when required to operate the service, comply with legal obligations, protect the app, or complete infrastructure tasks like hosting, database storage, or email delivery.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Retention And Security</h2>
      <p>Information is retained for as long as needed to operate the service, maintain account history, and satisfy legal or security requirements. Reasonable administrative and technical safeguards are used, but no system can promise absolute security.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Your Choices</h2>
      <p>You can update certain account information inside the app. If you want your account and associated tracking data deleted, contact the app operator directly.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about this policy should go to the Bankroll IQ operator through the support channel you publish with the product launch.</p>
    </section>
